org.eclipse.keyple.core.seproxy.message

Interface ProxyReader

  • All Superinterfaces:
    SeReader
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SmartSelectionReader
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLocalReader, AbstractObservableLocalReader, AbstractReader

    public interface ProxyReader
extends SeReader
    A ProxyReader is an SeReader with methods for communicating with SEs.

    Exchanges are made using SeRequest which in return result in SeResponse.
    The SeRequest optionally carries SE selection data and an APDU list.
    The SeResponse contains the result of the selection and the responses to the APDUs.

    The SeRequest are transmitted individually (transmitSeRequest(SeRequest, ChannelControl) or by a list transmitSeRequests(List, MultiSeRequestProcessing, ChannelControl) allowing applications to provide several selection patterns with various options.

    releaseChannel() is used to control the closing of logical and physical channels taking into account the observation mechanisms potentially in progress.

    Since:
    0.9

      • transmitSeRequests

        java.util.List<SeResponse> transmitSeRequests(java.util.List<SeRequest> seRequests,
                                              MultiSeRequestProcessing multiSeRequestProcessing,
                                              ChannelControl channelControl)
        Transmits the list of SeRequest and gets in return a list of SeResponse.

        The actual processing of each SeRequest is similar to that performed by transmitSeRequest(SeRequest, ChannelControl) (see this method for further explanation of how the process works).

        If the multiSeRequestProcessing parameter equals to MultiSeRequestProcessing.FIRST_MATCH, the iteration over the SeRequest list is interrupted at the first processing that leads to an open logical channel state. In this case, the list of SeResponse may be shorter than the list of SeRequests provided as input.

        If it equals to MultiSeRequestProcessing.PROCESS_ALL, all the SeRequest are processed and the logical channel is closed after each process.
        The physical channel is managed by the ChannelControl parameter as in transmitSeRequest(SeRequest, ChannelControl).

        In the case of a selection specifying a card protocol, it is imperative to activate it previously with the method SeReader.activateProtocol(String, String). An IllegalStateException exception will be thrown in case of inconsistency.

        Parameters:
        seRequests - A not empty SeRequest list.
        multiSeRequestProcessing - The multi se processing flag (must be not null).
        channelControl - indicates if the physical channel has to be closed at the end of the processing (must be not null).
        Returns:
        A not null response list (can be empty).
        Throws:
        KeypleReaderIOException - if the communication with the reader or the SE has failed
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the arguments is null.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - in case of configuration inconsistency.
        Since:
        0.9

      • transmitSeRequest

        SeResponse transmitSeRequest(SeRequest seRequest,
                             ChannelControl channelControl)
        Transmits a single SeRequest passed as an argument and returns a SeResponse.

        The process includes the following steps:

        • Open the physical channel if it is not already open.
        • If the SeRequest contains a non null SeSelector. The 3 following operations are performed in this order:
          1. If specified, check SE protocol (compare the specified protocol with the current protocol).
          2. If specified, check the ATR (test the received ATR with the regular expression from the filter)
          3. If specified, select the application by AID
          If one of the 3 operations fails, then an empty response containing the selection status is returned.
          If all executed operations are successful then a selection status is created with the corresponding data (ATR and/or FCI) and the hasMatched flag true.
        • If the SeRequest contains a list of APDUs to send (ApduRequest) then each APDU is sent to the SE and its response (ApduResponse is added to a new list.
        • Closes the physical channel if the ChannelControl is ChannelControl.CLOSE_AFTER.
        • Returns a SeResponse containing:
          • a boolean giving the current logical channel status.
          • a boolean giving the previous logical channel status.
          • if a selection has been made (SeSelector not null) a SelectionStatus object containing the elements resulting from the selection.
          • if APDUs have been transmitted to the SE, the list of responses to these APDUs.
        Note: in case of a communication error when sending an APDU an KeypleReaderIOException exception is thrown. Responses to previous APDUs are attached to this exception.
        This allows the calling application to be tolerant to SE tearing and to recover a partial response to the SeRequest.
        Parameters:
        seRequest - The SeRequest to be processed (must be not null).
        channelControl - indicates if the physical channel has to be closed at the end of the processing (must be not null).
        Returns:
        seResponse A not null SeResponse.
        Throws:
        KeypleReaderIOException - if the communication with the reader or the SE has failed
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the arguments is null.
        Since:
        0.9

      • releaseChannel

        void releaseChannel()
        Release the communication channel previously established with the SE.

        If the ProxyReader is not observable the logical and physical channels must be closed instantly.
        If the ProxyReader is observable, the closure of both channels must be the result of the completion of a removal sequence. TODO check how to make this conditional on the WAIT_FOR_SE_PROCESSING state.

        Since:
        1.0
